# Treat everything under src/ as bytes — do not normalize line endings.
# src/ is a pristine snapshot of upstream tbsdtv/linux_media; some files
# (notably tbsci.c, tbsecp3-ci.c) have CRLF endings from the original
# authors. Preserving them keeps src/ byte-identical to upstream so we
# can cleanly diff against it.
src/** -text
